\p
\v 1 My brothers¦148386 and sisters, not everyone should desire to be a teacher because we¦148392 know that us teachers¦148384 will be judged more strictly.
\v 2 We all stumble in many ways¦148393. If there was someone who never said anything wrong, this person would be perfect¦148404 and also able to have self-control over their entire body¦148412.
\v 3 With horses¦148419, we can put the bridle¦148421 in it's mouth¦148425 so we can make them do what we want, and so we can direct¦148440 the whole animal.
\v 4 Similarly, even huge ships¦148445 that are being driven¦148454 on by strong winds¦148452 are controlled by a small rudder¦148458 and¦148449 can be steered wherever¦148459 the captain desires.
\v 5 So too the tongue¦148471 is only small¦148472 but can make extensive claims.
